<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-08-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barrett</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-08-23"><hi rend="italic">August 23,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Barrett reports that the minister for foreign affairs unofficially
                            admits that the Varilla letter practically settles the port question,
                            but is not ready to officially concede the same. As the minister for
                            foreign affairs prefers that negotiations toward a settlement of the
                            question be continued here, Mr. Barrett suggests that the Panama
                            minister at Washington be advised in that sense.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>